# Predicting Interview Status (Machine Learning)

A machine learning project to predict interview outcomes (Selected / Consider / Rejected) using interview evaluation metrics.

## Objective
To predict the final interview status using structured evaluation scores.

Key features used:
- Logical reasoning
- Attitude evaluation
- Personality evaluation
- Communication score
- Interview duration
- Confidence and interaction
- Compliance ratio

## Dataset
Files:
- train.csv (training data)
- test.csv (testing data)

Target column:
- Status

Total columns: 27 (numeric + categorical)

## Model
Algorithm:
- Random Forest Classifier

Model settings:
- n_estimators = 200
- class_weight = balanced

Evaluation metrics:
- Accuracy score (80%+)
- Confusion matrix
- Classification report
- Feature importance plot

## Workflow
- Load dataset
- Remove ID columns
- Label encoding for categorical variables
- Train-test split
- Train Random Forest model
- Evaluate performance
- Plot feature importance

## Tech Stack
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-Learn
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Jupyter Notebook

## How to Run
Install dependencies:
pip install -r requirements.txt

Run notebook:
jupyter notebook
Open the file: Predicting the Status of the Interview.ipynb

Or run Python script:
python interview_predict.py

## Project Structure
Predicting-Interview-Status/
|-- Predicting the Status of the Interview.ipynb
|-- interview_predict.py
|-- train.csv
|-- test.csv
|-- poster.png
|-- README.md

## Key Insights
- Logical reasoning and personality have the highest influence.
- Communication and attitude also impact selection decisions.
- Duration and engagement have moderate influence.

